  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/intro/arch_overview/operations/draining has a list of 4 bullets describing times when draining occurs:\r\n\r\n* The server has been manually health check failed via the healthcheck/fail admin endpoint. See the health check filter architecture overview for more information.\r\n* The server is being hot restarted.\r\n* Individual listeners are being modified or removed via LDS.\r\n* Admin initiated drain via drain_listeners.\r\n\r\nHowever, the first of the two `drain_type` values, `default`, says that it applies to all **three** cases (not times) when draining occurs.\r\n\r\nI'm happy to offer an doc PR if someone in the know can make it clear what the behavior for default is.",
